msgid "**Behavior**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6558
msgid "``BEHAVIOR``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6562
msgid ""
"Snapping can be done to an existing node or a segment (its closest point "
"to the vertex to move). Available snapping options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6566
msgid "0 --- Prefer aligning nodes, insert extra vertices where required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6569
msgid ""
"Prefer to snap to nodes, even when a segment may be closer than a node. "
"New nodes will be inserted to make geometries follow each other exactly "
"when inside allowable tolerance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6573
msgid "1 --- Prefer closest point, insert extra vertices where required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6576
msgid ""
"Snap to closest point, regardless of it is a node or a segment. New nodes"
" will be inserted to make geometries follow each other exactly when "
"inside allowable tolerance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6580
msgid "2 --- Prefer aligning nodes, don't insert new vertices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6582
msgid ""
"Prefer to snap to nodes, even when a segment may be closer than a node. "
"No new nodes will be inserted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6585
msgid "3 --- Prefer closest point, don't insert new vertices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6587
msgid ""
"Snap to closest point, regardless of it is a node or a segment. No new "
"nodes will be inserted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6590
msgid "4 --- Move end points only, prefer aligning nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6592
msgid ""
"Only snap start/end points of lines (point features will also be snapped,"
" polygon features will not be modified), prefer to snap to nodes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6596
msgid "5 --- Move end points only, prefer closest point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6598
msgid ""
"Only snap start/end points of lines (point features will also be snapped,"
" polygon features will not be modified), snap to closest point"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6602
msgid "6 --- Snap end points to end points only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6604
msgid "Only snap the start/end points of lines to other start/end points of lines"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6606
msgid "7 --- Snap to anchor nodes (single layer only)"
msgstr ""

